    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Parts of works or complete visual works employing basketmaking that uses a type of plait having two canes or willows twisted together in the same direction, so as to enclose a crossing weft at each half-turn. Examples of fitched works include baskets and backs and seats of furniture.</Note_Text>
